<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="E" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Enrage" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Enrage,</orth> to put in rage, to make furious: <bibl n="shak. 2h4 4.1.211" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B IV, 1, 211</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 1.3.38" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. I, 3, 38</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 1.3.69" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. I, 3, 69</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 3.4.118" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. III, 4, 118</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 4.3.229" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 3, 229</bibl>. Partic. <emph>--d,</emph> 1) furious: <bibl n="shak. luc 1562" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 1562</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 2.6.38" default="NO" valid="yes">Gentl. II, 6, 38</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ado 3.3.170" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado III, 3, 170</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 5.81" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. V, 81</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 2.451" default="NO" valid="yes">John II, 451</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 5.2.57" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2, 57</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 1.1.152" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B I, 1, 152</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 3.3.25" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 III, 3, 25</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 1.1.124" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A I, 1, 124</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 4.2.75" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. IV, 2, 75</bibl> <cit><quote>(thereat).</quote> <bibl n="shak. lr 4.6.71" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 6, 71</bibl></cit> (Qq <cit><quote>enridged).</quote> <bibl n="shak. ant 4.12.31" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. IV, 12, 31</bibl></cit> <emph>(against).</emph> -- 2) raging as in a fever: <cit><quote>being now --d with grief,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h4 1.1.144" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B I, 1, 144</bibl></cit>. 3) mad with love and desire: <cit><quote>being so --d, desire doth lend her force,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ven 29" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 29</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>his love, perceiving how he is --d,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ven 29" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 29</bibl></cit> <cit><quote>she loves him with an --d affection,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ado 2.3.105" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado II, 3, 105</bibl></cit>.
